  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is Romania's 1% micro-company tax?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Romania allows companies with under €500,000 revenue to pay just 1% tax on turnover (instead of profit). Freelancers can set up an SRL (Romanian LLC) and bill through it. This requires local setup, accounting, and specific conditions—consult a Romanian tax advisor.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I renew Romania's Digital Nomad Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, once. The initial visa is for 1 year and can be renewed for a second year (2 years total). After that, you'd need to apply through a different visa category for longer stays.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Romania in the Schengen Area?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Not yet. Romania is an EU member but not in Schengen (expected to join 2024-2025). This means your Romanian residence permit doesn't grant automatic Schengen travel rights. You can still travel to Schengen countries but follow standard entry rules for your nationality.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is SafetyWing accepted for Romania's DNV?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Generally yes. Romania's insurance requirements are less specific than some countries. SafetyWing and other international travel medical insurance are typically accepted. Local Romanian insurance is also an option and often cheaper.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How is the internet in Romania?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Excellent—Romania consistently ranks top 5 globally for internet speed. Fiber connections are widespread and cheap (€10-15/month for gigabit). This is a major draw for remote workers.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Which city is best for digital nomads in Romania?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Bucharest has the most services, coworking spaces, and international community. Cluj-Napoca is smaller but has a strong tech scene and university atmosphere. Timișoara and Brașov are growing alternatives. All have excellent internet.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

